messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Go to the bathroom.
Go to the bathroom, are you in it?
How did it 9-1-1-1?
This is 9-1-1, what is your emergency?
East Edwards, shots have been fired.
Where are you? What is the exact address?
I'm at East Edgewood.
He's fired in a driveway, right across the street.
Okay, what's he shooting at?
He's shooting at me.
He's shooting at me.
I've been shot. She's been shot. He's on the ground. We're in the driveway.
Who is that?
He shot into the wall. Scott Eric Schmidt. He had a gun. He has shot me. He has shot her. He's on the ground. There are two little kids here. Please hurry.
Are they both outside?
What?
Are they both outside?
Yes, they're in the driveway. I've got the two little kids in the house. Please.
Okay, I'm sending help now. Do you know what the exact address is?
Calm down to me, okay?
Oh my God, they're here.
What is the exact address?
9-09 East Edgewood.
That's your address, right? What's their address?
That's not. That's your address. He's still got the gun.
Okay. Where did he go?
He's in the driveway with her.
Oh my God. He's got it. Please hurry.
Someone is on the way, okay? Try to stay calm.
Oh my God. Everyone is everywhere. We knew he was going to do this. We knew.
Who lives there?
My son-in-law. My daughter's house.
Do you think he's out there now with her?
He shot me in the chest. He shot.
Are you there now?
No, no. I got out.
Is she breathing?
He was in the driveway. He still got the gun.
Okay. Stay calm. Help is on the way.
He still got the gun in the driveway.
Is it a medical call now?
It's my son-in-law.
So it's a male, not a female?
My God! Ma'am, help me here. Is it a male or female?
A female. My daughter. She has blood everywhere. Please.
You've got two people that are shot or one?
Yeah, two.
What do you now?
He's not supposed to have any guns. He's on probation.
What is his name?
Scott Eric Schmidt.
And where did he go with the gun?
He's in the driveway.
What kind of gun is it?
A small handgun, I don't know guns.
What's he wearing?
A navy blue fire department jacket.
A blue fire department jacket? Okay. They're on the way, ma'am, stay with me, okay?
Are you injured, ma'am?
Yes, he shot me in the chest.
Okay, all right.
Oh my God, you bastard. You son of a gun!
I need you to get away from him right now.
Ma'am, ma'am, get away from him.
Oh my God, he did it. He did it.
Oh my God, Kelly!
Kelly's your daughter?
It's my daughter. My daughter.
What's Kelly's last name?
Kelly Wing. Scott Schmidt.
Kelly, are you all right?
Is she awake? Can you tell me if she's breathing?
Oh my God. My God, I don't know.
Ma'am, then go down and look at her. I need you to tell me.
Tell me, I need information from you. You've got to help me understand.
Ask me what you want.
Tell me if she is breathing.
She just gasped?
So she is breathing?
Yes.
Where did he go?
I don't know. He came out of the door with the gun, shot her. She was on the ground. She yelled at me to get out of here, but I tried to protect her and he got me.
Okay. He had a plan. He knew what he was doing.
Yes. That son of a bitch.
What is your name?
My name is Barbara Wing.
Barbara Wing, all right. Help is on the way.
Oh my God. Please hurry.
I know. Stay with me. Do not engage with him, okay?
There's so much blood everywhere. I love you, honey.
Did he go back inside?
No, he's by the car.
Okay, the police are on the way now.
Oh my God. He shot her a couple of times and then... he got me.
Is she breathing now?
I don't know.
Check if her chest is rising for me, okay?
Okay.
Are those two little children your grandchildren?
All of my grandchildren are here.
They are there? Are they inside the house?
Yes, they're inside.
Are you injured?
Yes, he shot me. It burns.
Okay. Are you talking with an officer now?
Yes.
I'm going to let you go then, okay?
Okay. There are two little kids inside. One and four years old.
